message_1: Consider a simplicial complex with 6 vertices, 9 edges, and 4 two-dimensional faces. Find the number of one-dimensional faces in this simplicial complex.
message_2: The problem statement already provides the number of one-dimensional faces. A one-dimensional face in a simplicial complex is an edge. Since there are 9 edges in this simplicial complex, there are 9 one-dimensional faces.
